

                                    Angular - Front End Technology

                              -------------------------------------------

                                         Basic Commands
                                   ----------------------------

            1. To create project - ng new project-name /  ng new project-name --routing

            2. Component creation - ng g c Component-name

            3. To Run Angular App- ng serve / ng serve --open

            4. Service creation - ng g s service-name

            5. Directive creation - ng g d Directive-name

                                        Basic Concepts
                                   -------------------------

          1. Components - { html,CSS,TS file- Class file} - Root Component - AppComponent

          2. Module - Add 3rd party library to project- Root Module - AppModule

          3. Data Binding- Communication/data sharing within Component

               3.1 One Way Binding - Data sharing in one direction

                    3.1.1 Component to View 

                         3.1.1.1 String Interpolation / Interpolation
                              syntax: {{expression}}

                         3.1.1.2 Property Binding
                              syntax: [Binding-target]="Binding-source"

                    3.1.2 View to Component

                         3.1.2.1 Event Binding - syntax: (event)="function call"

                         3.1.2.2 Event Binding using $event as argument -syntax: (event)="function call($event)"

                         3.1.2.3 Using Template Reference variable- syntax: #variable-name



               3.2 Two Way Binding - Data sharing in both direction at same time
                    syntax: [(ngModel)]="variable-name" 
                    - Import FormsModule , set "name" attribute if it used inside form tag

          4. Angular Routing - To set the path of a html page 
               - add <router-outlet> tag inside the root component html page

          5. Dependency Injection: data sharing between Component
               - inside constructor, syntax: class object: dependent Instance

          6. Angular Services - For redundant codes

          7. Angular Forms - 

               7.1 Template driven Forms

               7.2 Model driven Forms- Add ReactiveFormsModule 

                    7.2.1 Reactive Forms -  add validation 
                         {form group  - FormBuilder class,array -add validation, control}

          8. Angular Directives - DOM Manipulate

               8.1 Component Directives

               8.2 Structural Directives - To add/remove html elememts 

                    8.2.1 *ngIf - syntax: *ngIf="condition"

                    8.2.2 *ngFor

                    8.2.3 *ngSwitch

               8.3 Attribute Directives - Based on condition we can apply the style to html

                    8.3.1 Predefined/Built in attribute Directives - [ngClass]="condition? 'style1':'style2'

                    8.3.2 Userdefined Attribute Directives 

          9. local storage

               9.1 setItem - to save data 

               9.2 getItem - to get data

               9.3 removeItem - to remove data

          10. Parent child Communication

               10.1 Parent to child - Input decorator- @Input 

               10.2 Child to Parent - Output decorator - @Output

          11. Event Emitter - to generate userdefined events

          12. Angular Pipes - to transform data to another format

               syntax- expression | pipeOperator [:pipeArguments]

          13. Angular Animation 

          14. HttpClientModule import - to create http request

          15. Oberservable - used to resolve asynchrouns event
                    resolve state- subscribe()








